						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the temple of Durgā-Paramēśvari.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1236.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">26th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Siṁhaṇadēva, Manmatha, Phālguṇa ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1236, March 4, Tuesday.</hi> It records the death of a hero, <hi rend="bold">Masaṇi</hi> by name, in a fight when <hi rend="bold">Paḍḍiyadēva</hi> attacked <hi rend="bold">Ajaḍi.</hi> Paḍḍiyadēva is apparently a corruption of Pāṇḍyadēva (Cf. No. 219 above).</p>						

						</summary>
